The drummer is spring-loaded and equipped with a trigger lever in the rear. When moving, the cylindrical part of the bolt does not touch the walls of the receiver. - protrusions to hold the bolt cocked, in the front wall - a slot for the trigger [78]. In the front of the parallelepiped there are side grooves that have an angle of inclination of 72 degrees with respect to the axis of the barrel, where there is a bronze H-shaped insert, equipped with two protrusions that extend beyond the dimensions of the shutter. The protrusions are beveled back at an angle of 45 degrees relative to the axis of the barrel, which slide inside the grooves in the receiver when the moving parts move.